  "text": "As in Ref. [9] , we consider two sequestered sectors, each of which spontaneously breaks SUSY. Each sector has an associated goldstino (η 1 and η 2 , respectively), and we characterize the size of SUSY breaking via the goldstino decay constants (F 1 and F 2 , respectively). Each SUSY breaking sector can be parametrized in terms of a non-linear goldstino multiplet [CITATION_1] 9] ",
